        Even by recent standards this weeks chart is completely stagnant. But it didn’t used to be this way. I’m old enough to remember the top 100 back in the 90’s when it was physical sales and nothing else. The chart back then was never stagnant, every week there was a lot of new songs that would keep the chart fresh. Only occasionally would a song stay at number 1 for weeks or hang around in the top 10.

        It wasn’t all great though. Almost every new entry would follow the same trend, whatever position it entered at would tend to be as high as it would get then just fall down the chart. Only now and then would a song chart low then start climbing. So you never got the variety of chart trends that you see now.

        But it’s currently badly needing freshened up. Mr Brightside has been in the top 100 since the dawn of time. And who among us can even remember a week when there wasn’t a song in the top 100 from that warbling pest Sabrina Carpenter?
